{
  "_comment_readme": [
    "PrepX Concept Shorts — LTX-Video 2.3 ComfyUI workflow (UI-importable).",
    "",
    "How to install (side-by-side with the PrepX app):",
    "  1. Install ComfyUI:  https://github.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI",
    "  2. Install ComfyUI-LTXVideo extension via ComfyUI-Manager (search 'LTX').",
    "  3. Download LTX 2.3 checkpoint into ComfyUI/models/checkpoints/:",
    "       ltx-video-2b-v0.9.5.safetensors  (or the 13B variant if you have 24GB VRAM)",
    "     and place these into ComfyUI/models/:",
    "       text_encoders/t5xxl_fp16.safetensors",
    "       vae/ltx_video_vae.safetensors",
    "  4. Start ComfyUI (./main.py or run_nvidia_gpu.bat).",
    "  5. In the browser UI, click 'Load' and select THIS file.",
    "  6. Edit the green 'Positive Prompt' node — replace its text with your scene description.",
    "  7. Click 'Queue Prompt' — output appears in ComfyUI/output/prepx/ as .webp video.",
    "",
    "What this matches in the app:",
    "  - durationSeconds: 120  (length=2880 frames @ 24fps)",
    "  - resolution: 1280x720  (matches lib/video/scene-to-workflow.ts)",
    "  - sampler: dpmpp_2m, 20 steps, cfg 7.0",
    "  - filename_prefix: prepx/concept-short  (so the app can find the output)",
    "",
    "VRAM guidance:",
    "  - 12GB GPU: lower 'length' to 720 (30 sec) or 'width/height' to 768x432.",
    "  - 24GB GPU: keep defaults; consider 'steps' = 30 for higher quality.",
    "  - To enable the PrepX app to drive THIS install, set in admin UI -> ComfyUI Settings:",
    "      base_url: http://localhost:8188   (or wherever ComfyUI listens)",
    "      enabled: true"
  ],
